  "prompt": "How are style fonts added to an MIT app inventor?",
  "response": "Adding style fonts to an MIT App Inventor project involves custom font files and utilizing additional tools or extensions to ensure compatibility. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on how to do this:\n\n### Steps to Add Custom Fonts in MIT App Inventor\n\n1. **Select Fonts**:\n   - Choose the font(s) you want to use. Ensure they are in TTF (TrueType Font) format or another compatible format.\n\n2. **Add Fonts to Project**:\n   - Convert your font files to Base64 format. You can use online tools like https://www.base64encode.org/ to encode your font files.\n   - In MIT App Inventor, open your project and add the encoded font data.\n\n3. **Using Extensions (Optional for Better Integration)**:\n   - Use extensions such as Taifun's Textbox Extension or the Tools Extension by Andres Daniel. These extensions allow easier manipulation of text and fonts.\n   \n4. **Blocks Configuration**:\n   - Use blocks to dynamically change the font of labels, buttons, or text boxes. Typically, you\u2019ll use the `SetFontTypeFace` procedure provided by the extension to apply the font. \n\n### Example Using Labels:\n\n**1. Upload Base64 Font:**\n   - Convert your font to Base64 and copy the encoded string.\n\n**2. Add the Font as a Media File:**\n   - In App Inventor, go to Media and upload a dummy media file (such as a .txt file). This is a workaround to keep your font in the app assets.\n\n**3. Set Up Blocks:**\n   - Use blocks to set the font typeface of a label to your custom font.\n\n### Blocks Example:\n``` \nInitialize global customFont to [Base64 Encoded String]\n```\n```\nwhen Screen1.Initialize\n   call Label1.SetFontTypeFace (global customFont)\n```\n\n### Using Extensions:\n1. **Import Extension**:\n   - Download and import the necessary font extension.\n\n2. **Configure Extension Blocks**:\n   ```\n   when Screen1.Initialize\n      call FontExtension.SetFontTypeFaceFromAsset (FontAssetName, Label1)\n      call FontExtension.SetFontTypeFaceFromAsset (FontAssetName, Button1)\n   ```\n   \n### Deploy and Test:\n- Compile your project, deploy it on an Android device, and verify the custom font appears correctly.\n\n### Note:\n- Some extensions might be paid or require permissions.\n- Verify the fonts are approved for use, especially in commercial applications regarding licensing.\n\nThe above process should help you incorporate style fonts into your MIT App Inventor projects effectively.",
